import DocLayout from '@/layouts/DocLayout.astro'
import { productFacts } from '@/lib/facts'
---

<DocLayout
  title="Reports and data"
  description="Each report keeps source evidence, conclusions, missing data, and provider limits clear enough for another person or agent to check."
>
  <h2>Start broad, then narrow down</h2>
  <pre><code>seo report --project example
seo refresh-priorities --project example
seo quick-wins --project example
seo technical-watch --project example</code></pre>
  <p>
    The main report finds the useful next slice. Focused reports then answer a
    smaller question with less data and less noise.
  </p>

  <h2>What a report preserves</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Observed provider or crawl data.</li>
    <li>Derived findings and the rules behind them.</li>
    <li>Coverage dates, row caps, thresholds, and sampling limits.</li>
    <li>Skipped sections and the reason each one could not run.</li>
    <li>Provider errors that affect only part of the analysis.</li>
    <li>Commands that verify a fix or fetch a useful follow-up.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Report catalog</h2>
  <p>
    The local MCP catalog exposes {productFacts.reports} reports across
    {productFacts.reportCategories} categories. It covers setup and diagnosis,
    opportunities, crawling, monitoring, experiments, reporting, AI search
    evidence, and multi-report workflows.
  </p>
  <p>Ask the installed package for the live catalog and exact input schema:</p>
  <pre><code>seo reports list --json
seo reports list --category crawl --json
seo reports describe audit-page --json
seo reports run audit-page --params '&#123;"url":"https://example.com"&#125;' --json</code></pre>
  <p>
    The CLI and MCP server use one report registry. Agents using MCP should call
    <code>seo_list_reports</code>, <code>seo_describe_report</code>, and then
    <code>seo_run_report</code> rather than treating a copied schema as permanent.
  </p>

  <h2>Report accuracy</h2>
  <p>
    SEO systems expose incomplete evidence. Reports avoid turning rough
    heuristics into ranking rules, label estimates as estimates, and lower the
    strength of a conclusion when the input is sparse. Important changes still
    deserve a check against the live page and the relevant provider.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
